<br>
Maybe you don't want to share your great exp locations, but I'll ask anyway, where are the good places to try this? I'm lvl 60 now so I can't use the new PoP spells yet, but I have tried in PoD where the exp is decent and the small spiders don't have very high MR. I can often keep them charmed for almost full duration of charm after I have tashed them. Problem there is that its too easy to get adds there, and also pathing is very bad, once when a charm broke the spider was first too far away to cast on it and then it warped right next to me... So I often find myself gating away and not getting any exp for the mana and time I spent. If someone knows a better place to try I would appreciate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I haven't soloed much since level 10 or so, so if you have any tactics to share I would appreciate that also.<br>
<br>
Also are there any good places to use the lvl 62 charm, Beckon for soloing, or would I need the 64 one for most PoP zones?<br>
<br>
-Cerara <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadimemt>nadimeMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 423<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/21/03 8:56:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where do you charm?</span><hr size=1> I charm anywhere there are blue mobs not flagged immune. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227930">Nadime</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.furys-edge.com">Fury's Edge</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taserdevice>TaserDevice</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/21/03 12:32:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where do you charm?</span><hr size=1> Some of the spiders you mention Dispell, so if they dispell your charmed pet you are probably getting the idea that charm breaks more often than it really does.  <br>
<br>
As far as PoD goes, it's much safer to target mobs that don't cast, such as biles and rats.  Even the underbulks and lightcrawlers are better targets.  Although once in a while one may be a necro, most either aren't casters or are SKs, so you don't have to worry about them dispelling off your pet's charm. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cereberial>Cereberial</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Looting Highpass</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/22/03 10:58:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where do you charm?</span><hr size=1> At 60 best place to charm kite is probably PoN.  Its safe and easy, and you always have a res handy.  Only a few mobs in PoN top cant be charmed using Boltran's.  Once you get a bit of xp charming, head to PoJ.  At 60 Death Row is a godly place to charm kite, stuns land on the mobs there and you can make very good pp per hour.  To cut down time, invite your friendly mage, wiz, druid ... <br>
<br>
In luclin at 60 Akheva is a great zone, lots of spread out mobs that don't summon.  The big problem here is clerics don't come by that often, so when you die you cant get a res.  FG is another place to try, but is slightly harder than akheva in that mobs are more tightly wound.<br>
<br>
Cere <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=damindbomb>DaMindbomb</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturedot.com/FetchImageJPG.asp?ImageType=P&ImageFormat=L&ImageID=28408" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blackburrow Trainee</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/23/03 10:25:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where do you charm?</span><hr size=1> I am surprised no one mentioned HS.  With PoK stones this one has easy access these days.  Sure you still need a key to get in but worth the trouble.  The nice thing about HS entry...if you get into trouble all you have to do is run off the edge and gate  <p>-Juju-</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showPrevMessage?topicID=47.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showNextMessage?topicID=47.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.pwshift.com/tr/images/mt/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.emailToFriend?topicID=47.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.threadControl?topicID=47.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> 